                        </a></div></div><ol class="sense_single" htag="ol"><li class="sense" id="muhammadali_sng_1" hclass="sense" htag="li"><span class="sensetop" htag="span" hclass="sensetop"><span class="def" htag="span" hclass="def">(1942-2016) a famous US <a class="Ref" href="https://www.oxfordlearnersdictionaries.com/definition/english/boxer" title="boxer definition"><span class="ndv">boxer</span></a>. He was the world <a class="Ref" href="https://www.oxfordlearnersdictionaries.com/definition/english/heavyweight" title="heavyweight definition"><span class="ndv">heavyweight</span></a> champion from 1964 to 1967 and from 1974 to 1978. His original name was Cassius Clay, but he changed this in 1964 after joining the <a class="Ref" href="https://www.oxfordlearnersdictionaries.com/definition/english/black-muslim" title="Black Muslims definition"><span class="ndv">Black Muslims</span></a>. He had a very strong and confident personality and wrote poetry about his victories. He gradually became ill with <a class="Ref" href="https://www.oxfordlearnersdictionaries.com/definition/english/parkinson-s-disease" title="Parkinson's disease definition"><span class="ndv">Parkinson's disease</span></a> <span class="gloss" hclass="gloss" htag="span">(= a disease of the muscles)</span>.<span class="blockquote"><span class="p-g"><span class="wrap_open">“</span><span class="p">I'm the greatest.</span><span class="wrap_close">”</span></span><span class="footer">Muhammad Ali</span></span></span></span>    <div id="ring-links-box">
